	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64766182"><p><div class="quote"><p>Visa doesn't allow them to offer discounts when someone is paying by cash or debit card</p></div><p>I believe that federal law allows merchants to offer a discount for paying with cash, checks or debit cards. This was part of the <a href="https://blog.legalsolutions.thomsonreuters.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/durbin_amendment.pdf" title="thomsonreuters.com">Durbin Amendment</a> [thomsonreuters.com] to the 2010 Dodd Frank Act. State law regulates whether a business can levy a surcharge for paying with a credit card - some states allow surcharges, some do not.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64766182">

